The paper proposes a deep learning approach for time-series similarity measures, which is a topic that falls under the machine learning and artificial intelligence subfields of computer science. Specifically, the paper introduces a novel measure that models the alignment of time-series indices in a deep representation space, which suggests that it may fall under the categories of deep learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural networks (cs.NE), and signal processing (cs.SI).
